Okay, so... See this water down here? This is layer 3. Other layer 3 things can include cave and castle backgrounds (mainly in levels that use layer 2 in a special way), and also mist (like in the Sunken Ghost Ship).

What levels will we find on the other side of this star? Find out next time! And now, I'll just leave this map music playing for a while here. (It's Mario's Time Machine - Third Floor. Thanks, Zeldara109 and Glitch4Mr!)
Well, that's interesting...
If you wait for that bomb to blow now, you won't have to deal with it later.
Okay, now!
Oh, and I could break the entire level with his cloud, but I'm not going to, so I'll just throw the cloud away.
There is stuff up there, which I'll get to in a moment.
Okay, let's quickly get back to where I was...
Meh.
Oh, I'm sure someone could come up with a good reason to put lava in a forest.
Gah! Stupid Chucks. Also, I'm frying Lakitu now to remove him from the game and put him into the absolutely-removed-from-the-freaking-game-forever-until-I-leave-this-level zone!
We now return to your regularly scheduled Hacks 101.

Man, I'm just not with it when it comes to goal stars lately... Still, this is enough for a bonus game.

I don't think I've ever seen the game freeze from this, but yeah, it'll make Layer 3 vanish, which is especially bad if the level was making use of tides. So, place your message boxes (and world 1 Yoshis) in a side area that doesn't use Layer 3.
